                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d251">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/2107: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Officer in Chargé at New Delhi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-15T17:00:00+06:30"
                            >July 15, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>468. The following statement is attributed to Sapru as his considered view of the
                    general situation in India, “Jinnah is not going to get Pakistan and India is
                    not going to get self-government”.</p>
                <p>In a conversation with Weightman,<note n="57" xml:id="d251fn57">H. Weightman,
                        Joint Secretary for the Government of India in the External Affairs
                        Department.</note> Acting Secretary External Affairs, this morning, my
                    mention of this statement elicited an expression of his profound regret that
                    promises had ever been made and a prediction that “if they were kept an awful
                    mess would result”.</p>
                <p>This is the first instance which has come to the Mission’s attention of a British
                    official implying that British commitments regarding India might not be
                    kept.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Merrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
